# Trivy ignore — CVE IDs / misconfig IDs baselined with rationale.
# EMPTY on purpose: the first CI run's HIGH/CRITICAL findings get triaged into this file WITH a
# rationale recorded in docs/engineering/security-baseline.md, then the whole-repo trivy/image jobs
# ratchet to blocking. Add one ID per line, e.g.:
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX   # base-image openssl; no fixed version yet; not reachable from our code (2026-07-01)

# CVE-2026-39822 (HIGH, Go stdlib os.Root symlink-following, fixed Go 1.25.12/1.26.5/1.27.0-rc.2).
# Present via the embedded Go runtime of the PINNED OPA binary (opa 1.18.0-static, compiled with Go
# 1.26.4) in the api/engine images, and the webhook Go binary. ACCEPTED: os.Root filesystem-sandbox
# symlink traversal is not on any Norviq code path — OPA is invoked as a policy evaluator over an HTTP
# API with no untrusted-filesystem/symlink surface, and the webhook does no os.Root traversal. Revisit
# and drop this line when an OPA release built with Go >=1.26.5 is pinned (see security-baseline.md).
CVE-2026-39822

# GHSA-hrxh-6v49-42gf (HIGH, grpc-go xDS RBAC + HTTP/2 transport, fixed in grpc-go 1.82.1).
# Present via google.golang.org/grpc v1.81.1 statically linked into the PINNED OPA binary
# (opa 1.18.0-static) in the api/engine images. ACCEPTED: all three sub-issues require a running
# grpc-go SERVER — the xDS RBAC authorization bypass and the crafted-NOT-rule panic need the xDS RBAC
# engine fed by an xDS control plane; the Rapid Reset bypass needs grpc-go's HTTP/2 server transport.
# Norviq starts neither. The in-image binary is only forked as `opa eval` / `opa check` (subprocess
# rollback path), and the sidecar runs `opa run --server` — OPA's server is HTTP REST, bound to
# 127.0.0.1, with no Envoy ext_authz plugin (we ship `-static`, not `-envoy`) and no OPA distributed
# tracing configured, so no gRPC listener and no xDS client is ever created. Linked-but-unreachable.
# No OPA release (through v1.18.2) has adopted grpc-go >= 1.82.1, so a version bump cannot close this
# today. Revisit when one does (see security-baseline.md).
GHSA-hrxh-6v49-42gf
